               <p>It appear'd that Dent offering to sell some of the Prosecutors Goods, was taken upon Suspicion of having stoln them at the Fire on London-Bridge, but upon a strict Examination, he confest that Carr Halbert (who was <rs id="t17251208-13-deflabel63" type="occupation">Apprentice</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17251208-13-defend89 t17251208-13-deflabel63"></join> to the Prosecutor's Brother-in-law) got in at the Garret Window, took the Goods and gave them him to dispose of. Halbert confest the same, but said that Dent perswaded him to it. Both <rs id="t17251208-13-verdict64" type="verdictDescription">
